  "doc_id": "55341",
  "text": "Automated valuation methodologies undergo many development during the last years. Mass appraisal modelling tries to replicate market behaviour. AVM usually demand patterns for groups of properties. For this reason, they refer to large groups rather than single property. The multiple regression analysis (MRA) remains the most reliable automated valuation method [CITATION_1] , which was successfully applied, among other things, in constructing price indices in Geneva, Switzerland, determining rental values in Bordeaux, France, explaining the market in Tel Aviv, Israel. However, MRA has two known problems. First, the procedure requires, that the appraiser selects the best comparables. Second, it is significantly influenced by the presence of outliers.",
